UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2462
1 WHEREAS, John Dallas Stempel stepped down as Director of the Patterson School
2 in 2003 and retired as a professor in 2013; and
3 WHEREAS, John Dallas Stempel served as a trustee of Kentucky's Georgetown
4 College and, on multiple occasions, lectured at Oxford University as part of the College
5 and University's joint program. He was also a member of the New York Council of
6 Foreign Relations and a longtime member of Rotary International; and
7 WHEREAS, John Dallas Stempel died peacefully surrounded by family in hospice
8 care on January 8, 2025, at the age of 86, having lived a full and joyous life as an
9 accomplished diplomat, university dean, professor, writer, intellect, husband, father, and
10 grandfather; and
11 WHEREAS, John Dallas Stempel's mischievous wit, loving charm, and voracious
12 appetite for life will be profoundly missed, and his life of accomplishment and service is
13 worthy of public recognition;
14 NOW, THEREFORE,
15 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
16 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate Kentucky Route 1973 in
17 Fayette County, from the intersection with Kentucky Route 922 (mile point 19.205) to
18 the intersection with United States Route 25 (mile point 22.346) as the "Dr. John Dallas
19 Stempel Memorial Highway" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this
20 Resolution, erect appropriate signs denoting this designation.
